      "content": "It just feels like a lot of effort for something that doesn't actually change the outcome. Like, if the rebellion is so small and temporary, why is it supposed to be a triumph? It feels more like just prolonging the inevitable suffering. Sometimes it feels like the most logical thing to do is to just... opt out of the struggle before it wears you down completely. Wouldn't that be more peaceful than just fighting a losing battle against entropy?",
